Messages.Value: Thank you for calling our travel agency, my name is Sophia Moore, how may I assist you today?
Yes, I want to complain about my recent flight from New York to Los Angeles.
I'm sorry to hear that, could you please tell me more about the issue you experienced?
Well, my flight was delayed for over 3 hours with no explanation or compensation. This caused me to miss an important business meeting in LA.
I understand how frustrating that can be. Can you please provide me with your flight information so I can look into this for you?
Yes, it was American Airlines flight AA110 departing from JFK airport in New York on May 25th at 9:00am.
Thank you for that information. Let me check with the airline regarding this issue and see what can be done to address your concerns.

I'm sorry to inform you that the airline is not offering any compensation at this time. However, I can assist you with finding alternative flights or accommodations to make up for the inconvenience caused.
No, that's not good enough. I demand to receive some form of compensation for the delay. This is unacceptable!
I apologize for any inconvenience caused, but unfortunately, the airline's policies are outside of our control. However, I am here to assist you with any further travel arrangements you may need.
This is ridiculous, I demand to speak with your supervisor!
I understand your frustration and will transfer you to my supervisor. Thank you for contacting us.
